  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div xml:id="Aink1-kilavi">
        <p type="edition"> puṟattoḻukkattilē neṭunāḷoḻuki, ‘itu takātu’ eṉat
          teḷinta maṉattaṉāy mīṇṭu talaiviyōṭukūṭi oḻuṅkāniṉṟa talaimakaṉ tōḻiyōṭu collāṭi, ‘yāṉ
          avvāṟoḻuka nīyir niṉaitta tiṟam yātu?’ eṉṟāṟku avaḷ colliyatu. </p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en"> </p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="Aink1">
        <lg type="edition">
          <l>vāḻi yātaṉ vāḻi yaviṉi</l>
          <l> neṟpala polika poṉperitu ciṟakka</l>
          <l> veṉavēṭ ṭōḷē yāyē yāmē</l>
          <l> naṉaiya kāñcic ciṉaiya ciṟumīṉ</l>
          <l> yāṇa rūraṉ vāḻka </l>
          <l> pāṇaṉum vāḻka veṉavēṭ ṭēmē. </l>
        </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">

<l>          'May you live long, Ātaṉ! May you live long, Aviṉi!</l>
<l>          May many [ears] of paddy flourish! May the gold greatly accumulate!'</l>
<l>          That's what our mother wants. As for us:</l>
<l>          'Long live the man from the fertile village </l>
<l>          with little fish who have eggs and portia trees which have buds,</l>
<l>          and long live the bard!'— that's what we want. </l>
          
          
          
        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
